    <div class="container">
        <h1>Entrepreneurial Culture: Play & Creativity</h1>
        <p>A guide for maintaining human agency, original thought, and empathy in a world of generative automation.</p>
        <div class="audience-box">
            <strong>Target Audience</strong>
            <p>Innovation leads and HR directors navigating the "Human Frontier"—building cultures where original thought flourishes alongside AI automation.</p>
        </div>
        <h2>Syllabus Structure</h2>
        <div class="module">
            <span class="module-meta">Module 1</span>
            <span class="module-title">The Empathy Edge</span>
            <p>Defining the "un-automatable." Exploring how human empathy, context-awareness, and original framing become the new high-value skills as AI commoditizes content.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="module">
            <span class="module-meta">Module 2</span>
            <span class="module-title">Play as Strategy</span>
            <p>Using low-stakes experimentation and "play" to unlock lateral thinking. Designing institutional space for reflective and non-linear curiosity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="module">
            <span class="module-meta">Module 3</span>
            <span class="module-title">Resisting the "Average Trap"</span>
            <p>Ensuring that generative AI augmentation doesn't lead to mediocrity. How to use machines to raise the floor while humans raise the ceiling.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="module">
            <span class="module-meta">Module 4</span>
            <span class="module-title">Cultivating Curiosity</span>
            <p>Institutional design for "reflective practitioners." Techniques for keeping teams curious, ethical, and original in an automated workflow.</p>
        </div>
